"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-08-08-paris-2024-olympics-adekuroye-advances-into-womens-freestyle-wrestling-quarter-finals\", \"text\": \"Published  on  By  Odunayo Adekuroye has qualified for the quarter-finals of the women's 57kg freestyle wrestling.  Adekuroye sealed her passage after her Algerian opponent Chaimaa Fouzia Aouissi retired during the bout.  Aouissi sustained an injury which forced her to pull out.  Adekuroye will be back on the mat later today.  The 30-year-old is one of Nigeria's medal hopefuls in Paris.  She is currently the Commonwealth and African champion.  NPFL: Enyimba star, Daga sets target for new season  Paris 2024 Olympics: Nigeria 4x100m relay teams crash out  Paris 2024 Olympics: Nigeria's dismal performance worries enthusiasts  Paris 2024 Olympics: D'Tigress' Wakama wins Best Coach award  Paris 2024 Olympics: Brume vows to  bounce back from disappointing outing  Paris 2024 Olympics: Sports Minister apologises to Nigerians after disastrous outing  Paris 2024 Olympics: Team Nigeria officially finishes without single medal  Paris 2024 Olympics: Nigeria's last medal hope Reuben crashes out in Wrestling  Copyright \\u00a9Daily Post Media Ltd\"}"